<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-82-0223 </DOCNO><TEXT>Energy conservation measures, applications of nuclear power and renewableenergy sources, heat supply technologies, and ways to enhance the performanceof central water heating systems and to reduce emissions are pointedout. Representative energy supply concepts are evaluated under the aspectsof primary energy consumption, staff requirements, and cost. Reservesare mentioned. The Polish efforts in the fields of combined heat andpower generation and district heating are reported.</TEXT></DOC>